@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{citar-extras.el} extends @samp{citar}, the modern bibliography management interface for Emacs built on top of the @code{completing-read} API@. Where @samp{citar} focuses on selecting and acting on citation keys, @samp{citar-extras.el} bridges the gap between the @samp{citar} selection interface and other bibliography tools, particularly @samp{ebib}.

The package provides three categories of functionality:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Ebib integration.} Commands to open a bibliographic entry selected via the @samp{citar} completion UI directly in @samp{ebib}, or to navigate to its raw Bib@TeX{} definition in the source @samp{.bib} file (@ref{Ebib integration}).
@item
@strong{Cache management.} Commands to refresh the @samp{citar} bibliography cache for one or all configured bibliography files, which is useful after external edits to @samp{.bib} files (@ref{Cache management}).
@item
@strong{Visual indicators.} Custom indicator variables using @samp{nerd-icons} that display file, link, note, and citation status icons in the @samp{citar} selection UI (@ref{Visual indicators}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{citar} and @samp{paths}.

